1. Install the gh-pages package

In your project directory (C:\Users\ors_m\OneDrive\MasaÃ¼stÃ¼\mehmet work\son), run:

npm install gh-pages --save-dev

2. Configure package.json

Open your package.json and add these two things:

(a) Add a homepage field

Replace your-username and your-repo-name with your GitHub details:

"homepage": "https://your-username.github.io/your-repo-name"

(b) Add deploy scripts inside "scripts"

Example:

"scripts": {
  "start": "react-scripts start",
  "build": "react-scripts build",
  "predeploy": "npm run build",
  "deploy": "gh-pages -d build"
}

3. Push Your Code to GitHub

Make sure your project is already on GitHub:

git add .
git commit -m "Setup for GitHub Pages deployment"
git push origin main


(if your branch is master, replace main with master)

4. Deploy ðŸš€

Run:

npm run deploy


This will:

Build your app

Push the build to a special branch called gh-pages

5. Enable GitHub Pages

Go to your repository on GitHub.

Open Settings â†’ Pages.

Under Source, choose gh-pages branch and /root.

Save.

6. Visit Your Site ðŸŽ‰

Your React app will be live at:

https://your-username.github.io/your-repo-name